STEPS 
npm init

installed dependencies; 

npm install express 

npm i body-parser

npm run dev

create  route middleware == app.use('/api', )

Create 'routes' folder

Create this file 'home.routes.js' in the 'routes' folder.

require route folder and home.route.js file in the starter app

require express in the home.route.js file

create a new router from the express route

install environment variable using npm i dotenv, it didn't work , so i used npm install dotenv --save and require it on starter file with require('dotenv').config()

create a .env file, write your variables ie PORT and BASE_URL

create a controller folder and create news.controller.js file

create middleware folder
create a news.middleware.js file  